nodes.documentation:
A registrar that allocates subdomains and sets resolvers to the first person to claim them.

 * Adapted from ENS' FIFSRegistrar:
  https://github.com/ethereum/ens/blob/master/contracts/FIFSRegistrar.sol
nodes.name: FIFSResolvingRegistrar
register
registerWithResolver

register(bytes32,address).notice: Register a subdomain with the default resolver if it hasn't been claimed yet.

registerWithResolver(bytes32,address,add.notice: Register a subdomain if it hasn't been claimed yet.

params._owner: The address of the new owner.
params._subnode: The hash of the label to register.

params._owner: The address of the new owner.
params._resolver: The address of the resolver.                 If the resolver supports the address interface, the subdomain's address will                 be set to the new owner.
params._subnode: The hash of the label to register.
